org.morphml.networkml.schema
Class Level3Connectivity

java.lang.Object
  org.morphml.networkml.schema.Level3Connectivity

public class Level3Connectivity
extends java.lang.Object

Biophysics of Level3 cell, including specification for allowable synaptic locations. Note: from v1.7.1 the preferred way to specify a potential synaptic location is with a potential_syn_loc element under connectivity under cell, as opposed to the potentialSynapticLocation under biophysics under cell. The former will be the only option from v2.0

Method Detail

getPotentialSynLocs

public java.util.List<PotentialSynLoc> getPotentialSynLocs()
Gets the value of the potentialSynLocs property.

This accessor method returns a reference to the live list, not a snapshot. Therefore any modification you make to the returned list will be present inside the JAXB object. This is why there is not a set method for the potentialSynLocs property.

For example, to add a new item, do as follows: 

    getPotentialSynLocs().add(newItem);

Objects of the following type(s) are allowed in the list PotentialSynLoc
